OL,3,CInside story of surgeon who tried to
OL,4,Ckill colleague
OL,6,FThe judge also urged the jury to
OL,7,Fassess the prosecution's case with a
OL,8,Fcritical eye - they were asked to
OL,9,Fconsider an argument that Brooks acted
OL,10,Fin self-defence.
OL,12,FIn the end, though, he made it clear
OL,13,Fthat it was Brooks' choices which left
OL,14,Fhim in the position where he was on
OL,15,Ftrial for a serious offence without a
OL,16,Fdefence to put before the court.
OL,18,FThat would make this case unusual
OL,19,Fenough, but what makes it even more
OL,20,Fso, is the background which we can
OL,21,Fonly now report.
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4          G4/11
