OL,3,CInside story of surgeon who tried to
OL,4,Ckill colleague
OL,6,FStill refusing to accept food, he
OL,7,Fappeared weak and chose to lie on the
OL,8,Ffloor while addressing Mr Justice
OL,9,FPepperall.
OL,11,FAt one point, he became tearful. Asked
OL,12,Fif he was prepared to end his hunger
OL,13,Fstrike, Brooks said "I don't
OL,14,Fparticularly want to die, but if my
OL,15,Fchoice is between incarceration and
OL,16,Fdeath, I would rather be dead than
OL,17,Fincarcerated."
