OL,3,CInside story of surgeon who tried to
OL,4,Ckill colleague
OL,6,FBrooks applied to have the trial
OL,7,Fadjourned for four weeks to allow him
OL,8,Fto prepare his defence, but the
OL,9,Fprosecution said he'd already had
OL,10,Fample time to do this.
OL,12,FThe judge would only countenance a 48-
OL,13,Fhour delay, something Brooks said he
OL,14,Fcould not agree to, and the trial
OL,15,Fcontinued to its conclusion.
OL,17,FThe prosecution has consistently
OL,18,Fdepicted Brooks as "manipulative",
OL,19,Fsomeone intent on obfuscating and
OL,20,Fusing delaying tactics to frustrate
OL,21,Fthe legal process.
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4          G9/11
